Subject: [PATCH] feat(news): 'Latest' 10-day surfacing window on persistent
 bottlenecks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0088 implements the 'In play today' surface — show NEW persistent
bottlenecks at the top of each region panel for 10 days, then drop them
back into normal confidence/structural ranking.

EVIDENCE ACCUMULATOR
  PersistentBottleneck now carries:
    first_seen           ISO of earliest top_samples.recorded_at
    first_seen_age_days  days since first_seen
    is_latest            first_seen_age_days <= 10
  Computed in readPersistentBottlenecks() — proxy via top_samples since the
  raw evidence record doesn't store first_seen explicitly. Good enough as
  a UX hint; misses only the rare case where a multi-year bottleneck
  resurfaces with a fresh sample (which is the right behaviour anyway —
  the renewed activity makes it 'latest' again).

PERSISTENT BOTTLENECK PANEL UI
  - Section header: amber 'LATEST · N new in 10d' pill alongside the live
    indicator and India/Global counts.
  - Region dividers (🇮🇳 INDIA / 🌐 GLOBAL): per-region 'N new in 10d'
    counter on the right side of each divider row.
  - Card title: amber 'LATEST · Xd' pill on every card whose is_latest=true.
    Shows exact age (e.g. '🆕 LATEST · 3d').  Tooltip explains the 10-day
    surface window.
  - Sort: within each region, latest items surface FIRST (sorted by ascending
    first_seen_age_days). Non-latest items keep server-side confidence
    + structural ranking.
  - After 10 days the bottleneck loses is_latest, drops the pill, and falls
    back into normal ranking — exactly per spec.

Cache key bumped v33 -> v34.
